##"I'm not afraid of the plague. I'm afraid of my husband's abuse. "

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

The first contribution to "closure and mobility: China's domestic workers under the epidemic" came from Meng Yu. I knew that Mengyu had returned home from Beijing early to prepare for the operation, and I knew that her relationship with the countryside had always been complicated. I was a little surprised to see the title of the manuscript, "to the sisters I'm going to meet. ". I thought of something that had always been there in this "little journalist from the domestic staff" : When things change, she thinks about the rest of the group.

As much as I try to give you an impression of peace, I feel like I'm in a state of disarray -- a state of untrammelled longing -- as if this were my first reading. Could this be a trait that continues to emerge in subsequent articles? Let's see what happens.

As a tentative guide to writing

The first contribution to "closure and mobility: China's domestic workers under the epidemic" came from Meng Yu. I knew that Mengyu had returned home from Beijing early to prepare for the operation, and I knew that her relationship with the countryside had always been complicated. I was a little surprised to see the title of the manuscript, "to the sisters I'm going to meet. ". I thought of something that had always been there in this "little journalist from the domestic staff" : When things change, she thinks about the rest of the group.

As much as I try to give you an impression of peace, I feel like I'm in a state of disarray -- a state of untrammelled longing -- as if this were my first reading. Could this be a trait that continues to emerge in subsequent articles? Let's see what happens.

As a tentative guide to writing

The sisters I'm about to meet:

At this point, are some of the sisters already at work; some are back at work but still in quarantine, negotiating with employers about when to start; and some should still be at home, live the "eat, sleep, eat" special life you've never enjoyed?
Yes, the 2020 Spring Festival is an unprecedented festival. When I finally managed to buy a ticket home after a year of living at my employer's house, I thought I'd come back early and go to the hospital to see my long-delayed gynecological illness, at the same time to finalize the daughter's marriage, and then a good time with the old mother. When I got home, before I knew what was going on, the walls, the blockades, the villages, the vehicles... were escalating and isolating us from the outside world.
At first I knew the new term "COVID-19" was the night of the 12th month. After a busy day's work, I saw the news before going to bed, and I realized that this strange illness had been especially serious in Wuhan. Because did not see the relevant information before, also did not carefully look at one of the interests, think Wuhan is so far away, and there are a lot of treatment and prevention, it should not be a big deal? I didn't take it seriously. It wasn't until the morning of December twenty-nine, when I opened my mobile phone and saw the news that the city had been shut down in Wuhan, that I realized the seriousness of the situation.
Then, every morning, I wake up to the news that the number of infections and deaths is increasing every day, and my mood changes from insouciance to heaviness: Panic, fear, anxiety, all kinds of feelings come to mind.
Clean Kitchen (photo courtesy of the author)
I want to see my mother, want to accompany her, but the village is sealed, no one let out, I had to do. But call her and tell her not to leave the house.
"I'm eighty-five. I'm not afraid. I'M BETTER OFF DEAD! "
"Alas, mother, you are dead is good, but you did not see me, you are dead we can not go to bury you! "
"really? Is it that serious? "
"Yes, mother, it's the worst, the fastest, you mustn't go out, just stay at home, and I'll come and see you when it's over, okay? "
I said something, and let my brother and sister again to call her mother, this is to stabilize the mother. I know how she feels. How could she not want to see her daughter, whom she hasn't seen in a year? It must be hard for her to be so close and not be able to be with me. And as a daughter of me, it is not such a mood?
Yes, I came back early this year because of my daughter's marriage. Oh! Speaking of this marriage, I had planned to get engaged first and have the wedding next Spring Festival. After all, my daughter is still young, and I haven't met my future son-in-law. As a result, the daughter-in-law's family said that the next year is the birth year of the son-in-law, can not get married, besides, the two children have been together for more than a year, all aspects also quite hit it off. I see the son-in-law's character is also good, the daughter is also very satisfied, so finally can not stand the daughter's in-laws all the people of the reclamation, hesitantly held a wedding for the daughter on December twenty-six, in a short period of time to complete the marriage.
At that time, there was no news of the epidemic. Now that I think about it, I managed to get the two young people who were already in love to spend this special day together in this special period, what a beautiful thing it is!
Perhaps like you, I was busy with my daughter's business, and then busy with the purchase of New Year goods. We have a lot of good manners and courtesy in the countryside. We have old people in our family. There are many relatives and friends who come to visit the old people every year. Just as I finished everything, and prepare to spend a reunion year with their loved ones, only to know that the epidemic has been serious to the point of no contact with people.

In the village
Speaking of which, I think it's worth pointing out:
If you are already at work, then you must pay attention to safety, take care of your health. Go out to wear a mask, try not to go to a crowded place, if possible must wear disposable gloves, disinfection frequently wash hands, go back to change clothes. Many people in big cities and bad air, we do not have any security of domestic service staff, do not love their own ah!
Stay at home sisters, you do not rush to go to work, before going to be sure to negotiate with the employer, to be able to go to a safe isolation can give themselves a place, can guarantee to solve your Three Meals a Day, can you guarantee that you will be paid during the quarantine period? If these problems can be solved, then you can get a certificate of travel at your own location and take all necessary precautions (quarantine mask, disinfectant, hand sanitizer, disposable gloves, etc.) , you can go to your place of work.
If you don't do these things well, then don't worry, just stay home, relax, eat, drink, listen to music, dance, read good books, learn to write what you see and hear, and watch shows with your family, just give yourself a chance to recuperate.
Seeing the news of doctors and nurses who work day and night on the front lines, most of whom are not on vacation, are transferred to the places with the highest incidence and work in the environments with the highest risk of viral infection every day, some people do not even see the face of their loved ones, were infected with the virus and even lost their lives. I'm sure my sisters are as devastated as I am by this news.

In the village
Speaking of life, I've actually had some pretty extreme thoughts over the last few days. To tell you the truth, sometimes I even want to shout: I am not afraid of the epidemic infected me, I am afraid of my husband's abuse.
Truly, I was stifled by the conservatism of my family, and it was the grounding of the epidemic that made me see more clearly the trauma of my family, as if I'd had enough!
He does nothing every day (dare not ask him to do anything) , I do the work he criticized, I do everything he did not value, not only do not let me explain, but also in various ways to scold me. I don't like what I see. I don't like what I eat. I ignore him, he said I despise him this "head of the family" , as a woman want to "turn over the sky. ". Once there was no excuse, he began to slander me, saying, "is it the big city for a long time, there is a 'lover' in private. " If I argue with him, he swore with his family. Open mouth mouth shut"the outside of your whoring customers under the Sun (this is the most vicious curse words, meaning bastard) ..."do you say infuriating?
What's even sadder is the notion of family. Just back home, my head was still confused by the bump of the train, and my body was still tired from the long journey, they put a bunch of stuff out there waiting for you: "You're back, do this, do that... " "it's all women's work... "
When you are not used to the environment you haven't seen for more than a year, they will say "ambitious, even their own home is not familiar with" ; when you feel wronged want to argue, people around you will say: "You have not come back a year, endure it! " "often outside, come back well. " "Men are angry, women have to endure! Isn't that the way it's always been? Why don't you come home to him often?"
Every time I hear such words, my heart will feel very sad. In fact, I am also in my fifties. Physically and mentally, I feel that I am going downhill. When I come back home, I want to be cared for and cared for, but it always backfires.
In the village, all I could hear were the voices of Kuaishou and Douyin, playing cards, drinking, chatting, and wearing masks. At home, I wanted to read and write, and the woman who came to talk to me said I was "too big for them" and laughed at me for wanting to be a writer. I looked out of place in their eyes. Mother-in-law said: "As a woman, do not do needlework, what to read? " "are old still write things to read, what is the use? DO SOME SERIOUS BAR! "

In the village
I can't get mad! Yes, I work as a domestic servant, I wait on tables, I get told what to do, and sometimes I run into things that other people can't imagine. From morning to night put their energy and time, wholeheartedly in the work, down-to-earth, conscientious, in order to improve their family life. But back home, do not get the understanding of the family is not yet, but also continue to serve.
And more importantly: You can't do anything else, you can't think about anything else. The logic is: you serve, and that's what you do. If I wanted to do something else, I'd be out of line, not like a normal person. That hasn't even changed because I'm financially independent. Every year to the family money not a penny less, but also bear with them that I "do not work" !
Every day of abuse and roll my eyes, let me feel that life has no fun, life has come to an end. This to put the past years, I have to go out to earn money, why suffer his gratuitous every day loser it? More than once, I felt that we, in a big city, could make money even though we were being bullied and told what to do. After so many years, we have been at ease in their posts, to adapt to the fast-paced life of the big city, but it is difficult to integrate their hearts miss, miss the old home life.
But back in the city, I began to feel mixed feelings and panic: the constant worry of a depressed life, and the possibility of a downturn in the industry after the epidemic, made me feel like I had nowhere to hide, do not know how to go down the road?
I'm sure you all have a lot to talk about, given the mood at home and all the heart-to-heart talk you've been through? I haven't seen you for a long time. I Miss Those happy moments with you! Hope to see you soon! Finally, I wish us all away from the epidemic, good health, good mood, all good!
Hug!
Love The rain
13 February

This is today's "Liaogan" : "Liaogan" is the first month of each year in our rural twenty-three to do the ritual of the God of plague. We lit the fire, the implication of a year of bad luck are scattered, safe and sound another year.

About the essay
Under the epidemic situation, the closed virus and the flowing just need seem to be full of contradictions at this special moment of life and death. As the most basic working women in China, how do they settle their anxiety and anxiety? Beijing Hongyan Social Work Service Center, in conjunction with the pepper tribe, launched a graphic and video call-up for "closure and mobility: China's domestic workers in an epidemic situation" to listen to the domestic workers' sisters tell their stories.
